com.aionemu.gameserver.dataholders
Class DataLoader

java.lang.Object
  com.aionemu.gameserver.dataholders.DataLoader

abstract class DataLoader
extends java.lang.Object

This class is responsible for loading data from static .txt files.
It's used as base class of NpcData and SpawnData.

NOTICE: This class is used temporarily and later will be removed and npc and spawn data will be loaded with xml loader.

Do not use this class for anything else than NpcData or SpawnData

Author:
Luno

Method Detail

loadData

protected void loadData()
This method is supposed to be called from subclass to initialize data loading process.

This method is using file given in the constructor to load the data and there are two possibilities:
  • Given file is file is in deed the file then it's forwarded to loadFile(File) method
  • Given file is a directory, then this method is obtaining list of all visible .txt files in this directory and subdirectiores ( except hidden ones and those named "new" ) and call loadFile(File) for each of these files.

loadFile

private void loadFile(java.io.File file)
This method is loading data from particular .txt file.

Parameters:
file - a file which the data is loaded from.
The method is loading the file row by row, omitting those started with "#" sign.
Every read row is then forwarded to parse(String) method, which should be overriden in subclcass.

parse

protected abstract void parse(java.lang.String dataEntry)
This method must be overriden in every subclass and is responsible for parsing given dataEntry String which represents one row from data file.

Parameters:
dataEntry - A String containing data about a data entry, that is to be parsed by this method.

saveData

public boolean saveData()
Saves data to the file. Used only by SpawnData.

Returns:
true if the data was successfully saved, false - if some error occurred.

getSaveFile

protected abstract java.lang.String getSaveFile()
Name of the file which is used to store data in.
This method must be overriden in sublass if we want to be able to store its data. It's used only in SpawnData and should not be used anywhere else.

Returns:
name of the file
